\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid14957223 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What's your full name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Helen - my - my - I was Helen - Brodie Cunningham before I was married. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your present address is Balmwell House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. No. Yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And you were married? What year were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 1913.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You were born in 1885, where}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10818560\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 about were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I was born at Aberlady - in - East Lothian, but we came to Edinburgh when I was four years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well we lived in Albert Place, down East - Leith Walk way. Yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How long did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, I - I was in service before my people moved fro
m there. And they moved to Wheatfield Road when the new houses were made at Gorgie Road, my people moved then, but I was in service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You didn't actually stay in Wheatfield Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I never - no. Just my parents, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember why you moved from Aberlady to Edinburgh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well - my father was a postman and I don't - I think my mother was delicate you see, she died, I didn't know my mother at all, she was only twenty-four when she died, and my father was a postman and he had long distan
ces to go and leave for ours. See in the country at that time there were no motors, there were no - conveyance at all and they'd to walk to villages oh miles away, was away practically all day, and I think that they moved - for to try and - get something 
- you know - close at hand where he wouldn't be so long away, with my mother died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did she die before you left Aberlady?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, before we left Aberlady. But we moved to Aberlady and my - father - had an aunt kept house for him, and we moved, they'
d arranged - they'd arranged this sort of move - before my mother died, she died I think pretty suddenly in the end, I was just a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember why your father moved from Albert Place to Wheatfield?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I think just to get a newer house, you know more - convenient, yes, uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - my first - my own sister, I'd only one. A year and a half older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What was her name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Mary Cunningham, she died - she was a Mrs. McRae 
and she died in California. She was forty years away when she came and visit - to stay with me for nine weeks. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you recognize her after all that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - of course we were very like, we were near each other in ages and we were very
 like to look at, and somehow when she come off the plane - you just knew her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She died recently did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh no, twelve years ago. She was only seventy-three, oh it must be more. She was only seventy-three when she died, she went back in California of course. Died with a heart attack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember when she left school what job she took?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, she was in - service too, with a Mrs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3555757\charrsid9520696 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696  Winter in - in Thurlston Road, fifteen Thurlston Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was she always in domestic service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Always in domestic service, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Until she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She married - she was - latter - her last place as at - she was at a table maid in Asco}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8024694\charrsid9520696 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696  House at Rothsay and she married the gard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3555757\charrsid9520696 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 ner there, but she went out six month before her. He'd a brother there to California and she followed him in six month, and of course I never saw her for thirty-nine year. Mm hm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That was your own sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I had two step-sisters. Well I have not now. One of them died six years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your father married again after you mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
My father married again, yes. And the sisters are quite a bit younger than me of course, 'cos he was a while, and one them - the - the - one of them was never - is never married, she's still in Jura, and other one marri
ed and - when her husband retired they went Jura because he belonged there, and she died there six years ago. But my other sister, her that's never married, she still stays in Jura.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What was her job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She was twenty years in the booking office in
 the Kings Theatre. But first of all, when she started work when she was fourteen, she started in the Evening News Office. And after a while she didna like it, she said that nobody ever got married in the News office and - and there were no - there were n
o
 advancement for her and she left and went to the Kings Theatre, and she never was married. And she went - and - when the war came on, and they were all having to give up their job, she got back into the News office and was there right on until she retire
d at sixty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And then she went to live in Jura?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
She's always - at always, was always with my sister, the - well, she stayed in - in the - Joppa, at the Milton Druid, but they went to Jura when my brother-in-law retired. I had them seeing me l
ast week from Jura, mm hm. But my sister, the one that he was married to, died six year ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What was her job when she left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh she was a shorthand typist. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And what did her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 In Civil Service, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Their names were what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Her name was Alice Cunningham of course, but she was latterly Mrs McIsaac.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And the one that never married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Jessie Cunningham.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you know how old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I think he was twenty-eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Originally? Oh well - he was born in East}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8024694\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Linton. But he was really adopted, I think his mother died at his birth, and he was - adopted by a family. Aye, well, let's take - he was born in East Linton anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And he was a postman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 My father? My father was a postman, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was he always a postman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No, when he came to Edinburgh he got into the office in Granton Gas Work, and he was there right on until he retired. He was very good with the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8024694\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 pen, a lovely writer and my husband was the very same. A lovely writer he was too, mm hm. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he have any casual or part time jobs as well as being a postman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No, never anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was he ever out of work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Never that I know of, no. Never out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your mother died when you were very young, how old was she when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well she was only twenty-four when she died. And - and - just a month or two - after I was born. She'd only be twenty - I should say
 twenty-four maybe, but I - but then - I know she died in the month of July and I was born in February. So she would still just be twenty-four I should fancy, I don't when her birthday was at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Where did she come from, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well I think her grandfather - was a Minister in Dollar at one time. Her grandfather. Yes. Mm hm. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you know if she ever worked before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well she would work but I don't know what she did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She wouldn't work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, of course she was - she was - had the - children - quite quick you see, my sister and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you were a child you lived really mostly in Albert Place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That - aye, that's the one that I was - up - up until I went to - work in service you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How many rooms were there in your house in Albert Place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Just this - what we used to call the parlour, and the bedroom and a bed closet place, and the - the kitchen. We'd no scullery there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The kitchen was the room that you lived in really was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The room we lived in, yes, and there were a bed - in the kitchen as I said, a bed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did anyone else live with you, your aunt lived with you didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no. When my father married you see my aunt went - back, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How long after you moved to Albert Place did your father marry again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh - well - I was five year - I couldn't have been very long, I think I was just about five or six year old, I think about a couple of year possibly. I think about two year would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Then his second wife came to live with you and she looked after you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye, she looked after - my aunt went back to East Linton, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 After your father married again did you ever have lodgers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Never - never anything - no, never any lodgers, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your step-mother, did she ever have anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Anybody to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, oh no, she managed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She didn't have a washerwoman to come and do the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Nothing like that, no, she was a very very house proud woman. Kept everything beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She did the washing at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh we did the washing at home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She never sent it out to a laundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Never - no, no, never anything like that, she did everything herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your stepmother or your father make your clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 My stepmother was very good - at making clothes, yes. She was pretty good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about shoes? Did your stepmother or father make your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no, no. They were always bought, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Any time that you were getting new clothes or new}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8024694\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 shoes, were they new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8024694\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh always new. Oh yes, mm hm. Aye, well we never - course we - you - we wore our clothes qu
ite a bit you know. 'Cos you grew out of them but no after you were fourteen or thereabouts you know. Of course I was away in service by then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your father help at all in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. He didn't even clean his own shoes. He never even cleaned his own shoes that I knew of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he never make up the fire or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh he might have put on a bit of coal or he might have done anything if there was any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He didn't clean it out in the morning or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no, no, no, he wasn't like that at all, not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How about decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Never had anything like that, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If there was any improvements needed in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, he never did anything like that. But my stepmother was very good at - papering 
a wee bit you know and that. She could do it, yes, but she didnae - he was wasnae - that type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he ever dress you or undress you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, not that I - never - I never remember him doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he ever read you stories at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I don't
 think - oh yes. He used to take us in his - on his knee - and tell us stories, he used to make them up, and when he - got stuck - he would say, well what next and what next? And he would, say, oh the band played and we all marched away then, and that was
 the finish, I can mind the finish of the story, with the band - the band played and we all marched away and get to bed then. Oy my father used to tell us stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he ever take you out on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, never minded being out on my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If your stepmother went out would he look after you in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh - well, I didna mind much about - him looking - I didna mind much of being bet at all, no that - you see in these days they didnae go out so much as they do now. They never went 
to any entertainment ever that I knew of. I never knew of them being in any theatre of anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about your jobs in the home, did you have anything you had to do regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, yes, we had the - always the dishes to do, my sister and I. Clean the brasses and take the rugs down in the morning, to shake.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you still do that when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That was your job all the time until you left home really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, until I left home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your stepsisters were much younger than you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, one - thirteen years younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 So you don't really know them all that well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well we - oh yes, I went - had a telephone and kept - all the time with them, and do yet, my sister from Jura was
 seeing me in the summer, this year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But you'd have left home by the time they were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no. No, I was still at home, mm hm. I was still at home when the - oldest one was born anyway. Uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have to look after them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No. No, I couldna say we had to look after them very much. Never were out - never went out and left us with them. Never mind anything like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever bath either of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Feed them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Nothing like that, no, nothing - oh I don't - I remember I didn't do it, I just didna do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you were at school were you expected to go to bed at any special time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well I expect we would, I didna mind - you see, we were - my stepmother is very strict, and if 
she said you'd to bed you'd to be - you'd to go sort of style. No argument, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did anyone put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I think we would go to bed ourselves. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember when you started putting yourself to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I just didn't - I just seemed as if I can always mind about myself then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you share the bedroom with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Just my sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it a double bed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A double bed, yes, a double bed, mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was that in a bed closet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 In a bed closet, no, they had the bedroom, we'd the bed closet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 After the stepsisters were born where did they sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well they slept in - in a - a cot, in the bedroom beside the - father and mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You didn't have a bathroom at that time did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, there wasn't a bathroom in the house there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have a tub or something that you had a bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A - a wash - a tub - along with the sink in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was there any special night of the week that you would have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, we'd always our bath - in a tub on a Friday night you know. On the Friday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How often did you get clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh we were kept very clean. I just - we would - well, we were cleaned every week anyway. And we were kept clean, she was - pa
rticular clean woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You weren't told you could only put clean clothes on after you bath then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, we were - every - every week we were - I think it would be a Sunday, we would - we put our clean clothes on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Where}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8024694\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
about did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did we eat? We eat in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever have any occasion when you would eat in the parlour at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well - at a very rare time when there are any special visitors the fire was put on in the parlour and that, and meals were put in t
here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 In Albert Place how did they cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I - it was - it was a kind of open fire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A range sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, it wasnae a proper range. It was an old fashioned fire and there was sort of a screen sort of came down - that you could 
pull down - pretty near the fire, and put up you know - it - a sort of open - two jambs at it, just like a wee range but not a proper range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And you would put the pots on these arms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 In the side, yes. Yes, yes. We'd no cooker but we'd a gas - Bu
nsen thing you now. We could boil a kettle on it, but we'd no cooker - at that time, in latter days -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about baking things, were you able to bake with this fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not on - not - not - my stepmother was a lovely baker of scones and pancakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But she couldn't make a cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No, never knew her make a cake. But she'd make the scones and pancakes on the girlde. In front of this fire. Uh huh. Oh she was a good - oh she was a good baker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember when you had your breakfast, what time in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, we'd just have it before we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did all the family have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well you see my father would maybe be out early. There'd just be my sister and I and - and the babe - the younger ones 
of course would - they would have theirs probably different times, they wouldn't have the same breakfast as us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your stepmother get up and make each person's breakfast as they came for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh she got up of course there were only the two - my sister and I, the other ones were wee you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But she'd make you - father's breakfast first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, he was out early of course anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he make his own breakfast before he went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I don't think so, I think in his day - he - she would make something for him before he went out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of things would you usually have for your breakfast to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I think it would just be - tea and bread you now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I don't mind having porridge at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 After breakfast you should go to school, did you come home in the middle of the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 In the middle of the day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What meal would you call that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well it was our dinner, we were - there were always soup. Soup. And - the meat that the soup was made in - potatoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You wouldn't have meat as well as soup?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Just the - just the soup and bread. Mm. hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have a pudding at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not unless at he weekends, have a pudding at the weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have anything to drink with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, nothing to drink, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Then you would go back to school and you would come home in the afternoon, did you have anything then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well we'd have our tea, at night. Uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of things would you have for your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, we just used to have bread and butter. And jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not a cooked meal at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not a cooked meal, my father had a cooked meal always but we didna, we girls didn't have one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have any supper before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well a drink of milk, before we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about on a Sunday, was there anything different on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, well my folk always went to church on a Sunday, and - my sister and I - cooked - the dinner. It was all - I can alw
ays mind, there were a cauliflower to boil, was in water and - the cold meat and soup to warm up, and we sort of - managed that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 So you always had meat on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And we always just had our dinner on a Sunday the same. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your stepmother make her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no. She baked - baked - scones and - and - pancakes a lot, she was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, she made jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And bottling fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No. No, didna do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Never saw anything of that, of course - I don't think we - ever went in much for pickles or anything. Mm. Mm. hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did she ever try to make wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no. Never made anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your father ever make beer at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have a garden in Albert Place?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If you bought vegetables and fruit were they fresh fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, fresh fruit, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever buy tinned or dried fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She used to buy - buy dried - dried apricots and make jam with that, mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 So you would never keep chickens or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, we never were really in a country place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever have tinned meat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was always from the butchers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, nothing - tinned meat wasnae popular when I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You would have meat on a Sunday and during the week you'd always have it in the soup?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was always made - it was alwa
ys made soup with a bit of meat. It was only - meat - then I used to go for it, beef off the runner I used to go for. Aye, and I just - and the soup was made with the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever get extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No. No, well I had a cousin - a gamekeeper, and occasionally we got a pair of rabbits from him. But no very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your stepmother ever go without anything so you could have more to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no, no, she wasna like that at all. She was a very hard woman, she was a - we werena - well done to at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your father get more to eat than the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes. Oh yes, he - he - he always got - plenty to eat, yes.
