\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Church of Scotland isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Church of Scotland. He was a very quiet man you know. Very very quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But your stepmother sometimes went with him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, she went with him, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Always to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And you had a soiree in the wintertime, what would they do when they had their soiree?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, we got our tea and there were games and singing and that. Oh that was a great night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have entertainment as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, there was - singing and that, yes, mm hm. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And you went for your Sunday school picnic as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Sunday school picnic in the summer, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you go, was it by train or bus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Now - train, it would be train like you know. No 
very far but it seemed a longer time. If we went to Juniper Green we would think we were away to America. Mm hm. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were there any other social activities that you took part in in the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No, no, we - we just went to the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You didn't sing in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no, we never sang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you know if the church had a temperance club at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I don't - never heard of it, no. Of course mind I was away from home - just after I was fourteen. But - what they m
ight have had after that was - you know, that's a - I was quite young you see when I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did anyone say grace at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 My father always said grace, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What would happen if he wasn't there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh nobody said it, we just - we just started without you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you taught to say prayers at night time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No. No, we just said our own prayers - at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you know if your father was interested in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not - very much, but he did - have a little interest, but he didna go into it in any big way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well he was Liberal at that time, but of course - it was - it was only Tory and Liberal - then, but he was Liberal I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you know why he was Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I don't know at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You don't know what influenced him to be Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your stepmother, was she interested at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - she wasnae interested in anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And your father voted at the general elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh he voted Liberal, did, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your stepmother go and vote at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I didna mind of her voting at all, I don't think she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 1919 was when the women got the vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, I wouldnae - I was away in - oh yes, mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You don't think that where your father worked in the Gas Works made any difference which party he belonged to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I don't think so, no. No. I think that - the Liberal - would be more - common in the Gas Work, than the Tories would be at that time.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It wasn't because his boss was Liberal that he had to vote Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no. Oh no, there were a great number of men in it. My father was in the office, and he - he first of all he was on the weigh
ing and then he was dispatch clerk, and latterly he was - a - a - an inspector. And my husband - followed his footsteps. Did the same thing, yes, mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your father ever work for the Liberal party at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, he never did then. No, never anything like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your father and stepmother didn't take part in any political activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Nothing at all. No. Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When your father wasn't working how did they spend their spare time, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh he just was sitting in the house, sometimes singing, he was a great singer. Singing and playing the m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid811345\charrsid9520696 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 lod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid811345\charrsid9520696 eo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
n and that but - and sometimes we went for walks you know, or take - take us a walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You said your stepmother very rarely went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She didnae go out to any 
entertainments or anything ever that I knew of. Not - when I was at home, but after I was grown up and married and - and - not - so very long before she died, she was very fond of going out with my two sisters, to - loved the pictures, in fact, when my hu
sband was in the army I went every Saturday night to the pictures with her. And she enjoyed that, I used to take her you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your father ever go out in the evenings on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Never went out in the evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He didn't belong to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Nothing any club or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he ever take part in any sport at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He didn't play golf?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, nothing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Or go to football matches or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He wasn't a betting man at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you know if your father or stepmother belonged to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I don't think so. No, I think that the - my mother was a - stepmother was a very thrifty woman. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She didn't need to sort of belong to a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I think that she would see that everything - we weren't in any debt or anything like that. Nothing lik}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid811345\charrsid9520696 e that. And there were no insta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 lments then. Of course never - in my life has there been because my husband didna believe in it either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You'd be closer to your own sister were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, the two -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 There was a big difference in age between the other ones anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 With who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 With your sister, with Mary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 With - oh we - we - oh, we was very - 'cos she went - she went away just to - after she was twenty away to California.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But up until then you were very close to each other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, but then - you see, I was in service in Edinburgh and she was in Rothesay. Bu
t - I saw her every year and she came on holiday and that and we always stayed up in Glighton and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you were a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh just other children in the street I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You played in the street, were you allowed to go and play in other peoples houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No. I once went into another - a woman that stayed below - asked me into her house to play with the girls, and my stepmother was very very angry, and I was never to do it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was either out in the street or nothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye, or in your own house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you allowed to ask people in to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no. Never had anybody in, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you were small what kind of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - peevors and the - skipping ropes and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have diabolo at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you allowed to get dirty at all when you were playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, we didn't - no, we kept ourselves very clean, we didna have any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you allowed to play with anyone you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, there were no restrictions at that. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You weren't told not to play with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, the people about us were all the same as ourselves you see. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You didn't belong to any youth organisations at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, you see - as I say, I was away when I was so young. There were no - was nothing like that then, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you were at school and came home in the afternoon did you have any hobbies then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. We had lessons to do and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever have a pet of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, we never had - no
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you collect anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No, no, no, nothing like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You would do your homework and then would you go out to play after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, we could get out to play until a certain time, and then we were cried up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You went for walks I think you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye, some - we went for walks -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you allowed to go for walks with other people, with your friends round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well we would have been but I didna mind ever being. No. But I - we would have been allowed to go with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you were young did you go to theatres or concerts, music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No. I - I was away in service and my sister was in service - when we used to go to something in Queen Street. It was like a cinematograph, but it wasnae a cinematograph. It was pictures you know. I can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A sort of magic lantern show would it be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
It wasnae a magic lan - that was no the name of it, it has a name. Mm hm. There - there were a - a - a man - a couple that stayed - on the same landing as us, and he was a waiter some place, and he used to go get these tickets, 
complimentary tickets, and - he gave them my sister and I went. My own sister, and we went to this thing in Queen Street. And - I canna mind what you called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of thing would the pictures be about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well Rudyard Kipling I mind was on r
eciting something, and there were - oh just a lot of nonsense, I - I - I can't - a cart and oranges full and - and you would think they was coming nearer you, on the picture, oh we was quite fascinated with it. But I - there's a name. Somebody told me the
 name of that no long since, and I canna}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid811345\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 mind it. Be before the really pictures - houses came in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever get pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Never got pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever get a spare penny if your father maybe had an extra penny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Bu
t we used to go messages for somebody, and we used to get tuppence, on the Saturday for going, but we had to give that in, we didna get to spend it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did anyone outside of the home help your stepmother to look after the house or the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She never had relatives coming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, we're just working people, we'd no - help or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She didn't have friends coming in to help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If she was ever ill what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, if she was ill - I had an aunt stayed in the town, and I mind she came, and - that, and she came when the - the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She looked after you when the younger children were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well she looked after the house you see, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have any relatives living nearby other than the aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - my stepmother had two - other - two sisters in the town, but - we had no relatives like that I know, near relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you see much of her sisters at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes - oh yes, they came quite often to the house. On a Sunday they used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your parents have friends coming to visit them much to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - not that my - stepmother had her two sisters, came quite regularly. But my father had nobody in the town at all of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No friends either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No, well friends, yes, maybe a young - a young man that he had in fact I think he'd been his best man at his wedding. He used to come always on a Friday night, I remember. He stayed in Murdoch Stellers, he was a
 blacksmith, and then - oh an awfully dark man, he was a blacksmith right enough. Oh what a dark - dark hair they were you know. Aye. Ford, Alec Ford, I can mind of him. He used to come every Friday night. But - my father being a sort of orphan himself, h
e had nae - nae relatives, real relatives you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your stepmother and father share the same friends or did they each have their own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, the - no - it was just the one - lot that came to the house, but nid they - you know hadn
ae a big house, anybody that came was just in the kitchen sort of style you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If somebody came to visit them did they get something to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, oh they got their - oh as I say my stepmother was a great baker of scones and - everybody used to love her - scones and pancakes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And that's what she would give them when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they come on any special occasions or just drop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, I think they might be invited or - mm. But no, no real especial occa
sions. There were no - parties for birthdays or anything like that. No, not they just passed like any other day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Would people come without an invitation or would they have to wait 'til they were invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I think they would come without an invitation. Oh yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about neighbours, would they drop in at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - one neighbour - was very friendly, well they used to go back and forward all the time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Would your father go with your stepmother if they were going to visit neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - oh I don't - my father didna visit very much. No. He didna visit very much. He was a very quiet man really my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 People often well us that in those days they made their own amusements, nowadays we're watching television or listening to the wireless.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Ah well you see we'd nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did they do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I don't think - we just did anything. We - we just - sat, of course I was away when I was so young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they ever play cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not in - not in my own home but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Or games of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No, latterly of course I played cards a lot, but - in my own home I never saw cards. I did - did see now - that's not right - on a - certain night in the week the neighbour next door might - 
her and her husband came in and they played a game, catch the tin they called it. It - never - catch the tin. Uh huh. A card game, yes, mm hm. Aye well, it's a - a - some people know it yet, catch the tin. At that time that was the game, there werena whis
t, never heard of whist at that time. No, never - no, no awfully long before I was married before I heard of whist. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about music, did they ever sing together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Nothing - they played the melod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid811345\charrsid9520696 eo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 n and he was a good singer, he used to sing songs to us you know, the old songs and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But they wouldn't have their friends singing with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No, oh no, we never had any musical evening or anything like that. No. Of course - you - mind you see my life - was kind of different, there
 was a lot of children was - being brought up by a stepmother who were kept very much - under the - I see. Yes, mm hm. Mm hm. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I see, mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Would you say that people are divided into groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I wouldn't say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 All people are equal are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well I should think so, to a certain extent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Before 1918 would you say people were all the same then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well I couldna just say that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Would you ever say anybody was a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well when I went to service - I went as I say to Sir Hendry Littleworths house, and there were a big family, there - there are nine - in the dining room every day and every night, and I would say they were ladies. Oh they were awful kind to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You say they were ladies, what made them different from other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well because they brought themselves down to your level. You know, they didnae say - oh I'm Miss Littlejohn and you're only a 
servant, you know. They - spoke to you - if they got a new hat they showed you it. And the youngest was twenty-six year old, when I was there. She's the only - only one left, I don't if she's still - but she was - a wee while ago, when there were a plaque
 
put on - their - at the house in the Circus that I was in, there were a plaque put on commemorate - his hundredth anniversary of Sir Hendry being made the - medical officer, the first medical officer of health at Edinburgh ever had. Well Miss - who was Mi
s
s Dorothy then, she's a Mrs Hedder was the only one married, Mrs Hed - well there were another one married a minister, a Mrs Hedder, she come from Glasgow and I was nearly going down to the thing, but I thought - I did - I don't know what way, I didna go 
a
nd I'm sorry I didnae go. Her photo was in the paper, and a walking stick and - oh, you know I just couldna get over it, to think when I - mind her as a young woman of twenty-six and - so smart and that and - there - then she - oh, and look with the Littl
e johns about her, I seemed to see the likeness and then her n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid811345\charrsid9520696 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
ece, there were another daughter, Miss Jessie, she married the minister of - of St Paul}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid811345\charrsid9520696 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
s, in York Place, eventually - he was minister in Collington, in the English church, at Collington, and sh
e'd one daughter, and this daughter - must - she must never have married for she was at the - her photo was in - and I can mind she was just a wee - she'd sit in a big chair when they used to come and visit and - you asked her her name, Helena Mary Harvey
 
Day. And if she didna like her dinner she just took it and threw it - over - one of these high chairs she had, and if her dinner didn't - she threw it over. She said, I don't like my aunt, she's cross, this was with - Miss Littlejohn like. She was really 
