\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you taught to regard ministers in any special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh no, we went to a minister at church, and the minister of Lawrence Street, he was a Mr Donaldson, at that time, oh I used to love to go and hear him - preaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you taught any special respect for a minister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, yes, my father always used to tell me that when he was a boy any minister you lifted your cap to. Whether you knew him or no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you ever taught to curtsey to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 To - oh, no, no, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your father was taught to lift his had to a minister, would there be anybody else that he was taught to lift his hat to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I don't think so, but - he just mentioned the minister, he always did I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you ever taught special respect for perhaps a doctor or teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I didna come much in contact with them, no. Not until I went into service with Sir Hendry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about shopkeepers, were they regarded as different from anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No, no, I didna then have anything much to do with shopkeepers really. You see, I wasn't anyway shopping and then I was away - the shopping was all done for you and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did anyone ever call your father sir or your stepmother madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever call anybody sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not until I was in service, we 'cos - aye, aye, it was said you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 In the district round about Albert Place in Leith were there any people that were regarded as more important than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, yes, there were some better jobs than others maybe, but - on the whole -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was their jobs that made them better was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, but they were all just in - we were all on the same footing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of jobs would be regarded as more important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well, maybe office jobs, white collar jobs would be - you thought they were maybe a wee bit better than the workmen you know. But otherwise, they didna make any difference to you you know, they all treated you the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of people went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Ah well, an awe - an awful lot didna go to church at all, but my father of course he was a great churchman you know. He was - church you know, always went to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 All the people living round about you, you s
ay they had the same standard of living, or were there some that were perhaps worse off than yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, we were just in an ordinary standard of living you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you know anybody that was much worse off than yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, no unti
l - at - at one - and there were a big strike on of some time, and - a mine - it think it was a miners strike, and there were an awful lot of people - out work, and - I know for the people were hard up then, but it never affected us, my father had always 
- steady job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember if people made any distinction between a labourer and a craftsman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I can't say that I noticed any. Can't mind of anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your stepmother and father regard people as all much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, I think they did. Yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you think your stepmother saw herself belonging to any special group at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. She - she was a great home - and - and - sewers, not - not knitting, but an awful go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid811345\charrsid9520696 od se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 wer and making - down things you know and that. She were as very thrifty woman, I will give her her credit for that, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you ever remember seeing a policeman around in Albert Place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A policeman, oh - we used to be frightened of them with the big mousta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid811345\charrsid9520696 c}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 hes, you know, they - they looked like policemen then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did you think about policeman at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh you just used to run when you saw one. Run and hid. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Why did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh just because you was kind of - oh they were a policeman and they were somebody you - got out of the way of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your parents taught you to keep out of the way of policemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I don't know if they did or - you just - naturally - you know, you were just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If you were ever naughty did anyone ever say to you I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, never had any experience -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did the policeman actually treat people at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I think they were a bit rougher than what they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever see them actually touching anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, I never saw anything - no, but - but there were far more policemen walking around than what there are now. Oh far more than now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your home in Albert Place, did it belong to your father or was it rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Rented. Rented. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever see the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well - I did - I had - I did see him - when I had once to go down - to - for the place was in - down about Iona Street or somewhere, to report the gas leakage or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of person was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh just nice and - to talk to you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He was a nice landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, quite a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A fair sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, quite all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your parents have a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your father and your stepmother have a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - they were - they werenae - too well off. No. But - I think they were kind of comfortable as - wages go at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What happened if your father was ever ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well as it so happened he never was ill. Never was ill - until he retired. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I wondered if he got paid when he was off work or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He wouldna get paid if he'd been off work, no, not at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You never got any help from any charities at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, nothing like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was there anyone in the district that the people really disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well, there were some people - that stayed beside us and the man used to come in drunk on a Saturday night and - and - talk loud and like that, well we looked down on them sort of you know. Mm hm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You don't ever remember anyone actually being chased out of their home because they were disliked so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, I don't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That did happen in some places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you given lessons by one of your parents or did you go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Brunswick Road. Yes. When we - when we came to Edinburgh first I couldnae get into a school. My sister did. But they werena an opening for me. And I went to a school in Easter Road. It was a paying school, St Margaret}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid811345\charrsid9520696 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 s you called it. But I was only there - until there were an opening - in Brunswick Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What kind of school was Brunswick Road at that time, who owned it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was a Mr Alexander was the headmaster, he stayed in Finthorn Place. Mind his address 28 Finthorn Place, uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it what they called a board school at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Just an ordinary school. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And it was a mixed school, boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, boys and girls. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of hours did you go to school, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, I think just the same hours as what they do now really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Start about nine o'clock in the morning was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Mm hm. I mind then our dinner hour was half past twelve. We - went home for our dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember if you went longer to school when you were older or did you always go the same amount of time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - well, no - all - we - I always went the same time, but them that stayed on after me, you see, I left I say 
when I was twelve. If any - anybody that was staying on after that - I think their hours were different. And of course they were learnt French and - things that - wasnae going to be any use to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You got out at half past twelve, when you first went to school did you go all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes. Oh yes, all the time. Mm. Yes, right from the beginning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What age were you when you actually started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, I wouldna be quite - I wouldna be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid811345\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You were just under five were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A
ye, but - I would be under five because we came to Edinburgh when I was about four. And - it - just seemed shortly after that that I started school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you went to Easter Road how did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Just - we - we went along Albert Street - and it was beside - Easter Road station nearly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You didn't like Easter Road school, and that was the one where you had to pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That's the paying one, yes, uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Have you any idea how much you had to pay at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, it wouldna be very much but it was - considered - quite a bit then, but it was only because I couldna get into the other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you actually have to take the money on a Monday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no, they - it was per - periods, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Then you went to Brunswick Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Brunswick Road, I - I think I was only a few months in St Margarets, in Easter Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You got home at lunch time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh just walked just up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your sister go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your stepmother ever take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It's not very far of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 We hadnae any crossings or anything you know to Brunswick Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You came home for your lunch and then you went back in the afternoon. You didn't like Easter Road, what did you think of Brunswick Street?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh I liked it all right, yes, I wasnae awfully long there when I took - I was off for quite a time with pneumonia, double pneumonia I had, I was off for quite a time and after I went back I didna like it for a bit - for Miss McIntyre was the teacher then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it the teacher you didn't like or just the atmosphere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Just the - at - I think, I can go back, and I didna feel well, I can just mind sitting in the school and no feeling well at
 all. Weak and ill you know. However - that passed off and I got on all right at the school you know, passed off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You said there was one teacher at Easter Road that you didn't like, what about the teachers in Brunswick Road school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well I liked them all right, yes, done well enough with them. I don't know - the one teacher in - St Margaret}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12541827\charrsid9520696 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 s, I did - while - while I was there, but in Brunswick in Brunswick Road of course there were different ones you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were they all much the same, the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - yes, well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were there some that you liked better than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, yes, there was some you liked better than others, but no, I got on all right with them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they emphasise anything as being especially important, such as manners or being tidy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. I don't think they went in for that in my young days, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it just the three R's that you were taught?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Just - it was just your - your lessons, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they teach you any special way to speak?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, she just spoke ordinary you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She didn't say you mustn't say this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, she didna - didna learn you manners or anything like that, it was only your lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well of course she used the strap if you - uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of things merited the strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - well maybe talking when you shouldna be talking or - and - not knowing an answer properly or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If you made a mistake actually did you get the strap then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh if you made a mistake you did, she was quite - good with a strap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were the girls the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Just the same, yes. The girls at the one side and the boys at the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But they all got the same sort of punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Same punishment and the same lessons and everything, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were your parents interested in your school work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, they were - because if - our marks werena very good you wasna very - keen to take it home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they ask what you'd been doing at school during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, they didna take very much interest in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they ever go up to the school to see the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - well once my father - went to see the headmaster about something. The teacher 
had - had punished me and awful bad, my hand was all swollen and that. And he went up, he thought it was - too much. But it only made the teacher take an ill will to me after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember what it was you got the strap for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh did mind 
- I didna mind at the moment what it was, no. Be something that I wouldna know properly right. Although I had lots of prizes, a Bible and - thi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15673613\charrsid9520696 ngs that I was quite good at how}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696  know. But of course there are some things you're no just so good at. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did the other children come from similar types of homes as your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, we were all much about the same. We were all much about the same, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did any of the teachers ever single out some children and treat them differently as others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Didna teach them different, she had her favourites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Why do you think somebody would be a favourite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well maybe - nice - very nice looking wee girl, you know, I mind the one girl - Grace Lock was her name, and - and she was an awfully pretty girl, and - and the teachers favourite her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Because she was well dressed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, but she was nice, pretty and nice, nice -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was she clever as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, and nice spoken, and I can mind when we all had a bit of poetry to say for something an
d somebody came in to hear us saying this poetry, I can mind my bit was the Boy Stood on the Burning Deck, and this - I dinna mind what Grace's was, but - he was going away, some inspector came in and she said, oh you must hear this girl, and she did - an
d you know she was such a nice talker. And such a nice wee - I - I believe - if I had known her - after, I believe - as an elocutionist she'd have been good. I can just picture her like that now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was there anybody ever treated the opposite kind of way, ignored?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, no, don't think so, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were there any gangs or groups in the school at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, we were just all together yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 People didn't form up gangs against each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no. If you were going the same way you went together going home and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were there any children who were ever left out of things altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever go on to another school after Brunswick Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No, Brunswick Street was the only one I was at.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How old were you when you left first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Twelve - just over twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You went to work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I went - it was a wee factory, and I - to pak stationery into boxes, and - the foreman - discovered I wasna thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was that the legal age at that time for working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
For starting to work, yes, but you could leave the school any time. There was no rule that time, and - he said that - that I would have to stay at home until I was thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You didn't go back to school then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh no, no, no. Oh no, it was only a few months it would be likely. And I went back when I was thirteen, and I was there until I left to go to Sir Henry Littlejohn's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Would you have stayed at school longer if you'd had the chance?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I think I wanted away, I didna want to learn French and the languages, I didna seem to be able to - pick it up very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever go to classes at all after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No, no
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you think you benefited at all from what you learnt at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well I've got through the world all right after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Have you any regret as about the kind of education you had at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, no now, because I got on all right you know, got - got an all right after I left and - when I w
as away from home I - quite enjoyed being - with other girls in the place, there were a few of us you know, of course I was young - beside them and - they treated me awful nice you know, they - sort of made a fuss of me, and I'd never had any fuss made of
 me when I was young. Never was petted or anything like that. But they sort of were awfully good to me you know and - I just knew the difference and - enjoyed it, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you were at school I think you said there was a lady gave you tuppence a week for going messages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was that one of the neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 One of the neighbours, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever have any other kind of part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, that was only just a - just a-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You never delivered milk or papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, nothing like that, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I think you said the tuppence had to go to your stepmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye, she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did she do with it, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh she - sometimes she put it in the drawer, and sometimes when I thought she'd forgot about I would take it out again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What would you do with it then?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you go and spend it if you got it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh sweeties with it, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You worked in the stationers again after you were thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 After I was thirteen until I was fourteen and - fourteen and a half or fourteen and three month really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That was when you went to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Sir Henry Littlejohn, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The job at the stationers, how did you get the job in the first place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well you just went along and asked if th
ere were any vacancies. They were always taking on young girls. You'd - three shillings a week was all your pay. But I was in the Littlejohn's I'd only twelve shillings in the month, and that was the calendar month, not every four weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But you had your keep as well didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You had your keep you see and your - and your bed and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 In the stationers what hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Eight o'clock in the morning until one, and then from two until six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Saturdays is one o'clock but no Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your half day was a Saturday was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever have any holiday with pay while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no. No holiday with pay, there were no holidays with pay - when I was young.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What was it you said you were paid at the stationers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
At the stationers, three - three and six a week at the stationers. And three shilling - and twelve shillings a month - when I was with Sir Henry Littlejohn, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were these fair wages at the time or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well it was just the ordinary, I think they were just a standard wage - for the - time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did you do with the money you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh just handed it in to the house. Just handed it in to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Ad it was used for the running of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye, for the running of the house, so that it could help to get clothes for you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 At the stationers how did you get on with the other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15673613\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well I was at a table with just other two, packing the stationery into boxes. I got on all right with them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You went to Sir Henry Littlejohn's, that was your first domestic service job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Sir Henry Littlejohn, what was his address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 24 Royal Circus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That was one of these great big Georgian houses wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, with the attics, the two. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You went there when you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well I was over fourteen a wee bit, fourteen and three month I think. I think I went in the May and I had been fourteen in the February.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How many servants did he have in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What were they, what were their titles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well one was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15673613\charrsid9520696 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696  table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15673613\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
maid, one was a housemaid and one was a cook. And - an under housemaid and me. Five altogether, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Where did they sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well - there - there were the basement - and we all slept in the basement. I slept in the same room as the cook. But you'd all beds to ourselves you know. Yes. It were quite a big basement you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Whereabouts did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well we had a servants hall. Yes, and we - we ate in the servants hall, I had that to keep the servants hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If you weren't working were you allowed to sit in the servants hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh that's where you sat if you werena working. Oh the others - 
but I - I never really had much time for sitting, but the others sometimes had you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you call them the master and the mistress or what did you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - Miss Littlejohn, was Miss Littlejohn - the others were Miss Dorothy, Miss Winnie and Miss Mildred.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did you call Sir Henry Littlejohn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh Sir Henry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And his wife was what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well of course his wife wasna there but she was dead long before I went. Uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 So who was it that actually ran the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Miss Littlejohn. Miss - Miss Littlejohn, Is - Isobel was her name, Miss Littlejohn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did she supervise the housework herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She supervised everything, the - tit - the - catering and everything she did herself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She would give you your orders herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She gave us the - of course - I never really had much talk, it was more the other servants that - I was working for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they pass on the information to you what you had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye, well I - I had my work, I had my certain work 
to - a certain day each week that you've something to do. You were upstairs helping the housemaids in the morning. I had the - the four youngest ones, Miss Dorothy, Miss Rachel, Miss Winifred and Miss Mildred, had their rooms to keep, that was two rooms -
 two in a room, and then - I - at dinnertime I come down, set the - dinner for - in the servants hall, and then I worked with the cook in the afternoon, washed the dishes and help her to make sauces and - you know, prepare vegetables and - that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was quite a varied job you had then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, aye. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you feel at ease with the other servants, you were friends with the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, they - they were awful nice to me, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about the members of the family, how did you get on with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh they were all nice to me too, yes. All nice to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did the servants and the members of the family address each other, what did you call each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, the - the ladies just - they called me Helen. Just my first 
name, we were all called by our first name. But if you were talking to them you'd talk - say Miss Dorothy or - Miss Winnie, you know, whatever their name was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were they interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I think so, I think in me in particular being so young. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did Miss Littlejohn give any moral guidance to her servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No. Miss Littlejohn - she was - we were all sort of under Miss Littlejohn. She were - she - sort of ruled the house. When we went to Arlech in the summertime, Miss 
Littlejohn didna go. And it was just like a holiday to me, you know. Because the young ones couldna have cared less whether you did anything right or no. But Miss Littlejohn was very particular.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you allowed time to do just what you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well if you just did - if you're finished you could do what you liked, but I was hardly ever finished. But the other ones used to sew and - go away you know on their own but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When were you allowed out of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Every - I - I got - one - afternoon in the week, you got off an afternoon and evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If you finished your work early were you allowed to go out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no. No, no. No. No, no. But you see, to be - to let you understand - I was never finished early, because after the
 dinner at - dinner at night, and they'd always a five course dinner, and I'd all these dishes to wash. And then after that, I had - the hot - the servants - dishes - we had our supper, and then that to clear away and wash, and then I'd hot water bottles 
- to take up the stair to the rooms, and that was a carry up, it was a stone - hot water bottles, up to the rooms, and then by the time you come down it was bedtime right enough. I didn't have much time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you had your day off did you have to be back by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
You were supposed to be back at ten o'clock. Of course - you - they never quite - queried you, if you were back at ten, but on a Sunday night they'd always prayers, and you had to be in by nine o'clock. And of course they knew yo
u're in for you to go up for prayers at nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever feel homesick at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no, I liked it better than my home. I liked it better, I felt more -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You didn't feel lonely at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I didna feel lonely a bit, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was there anything you particularly liked or disliked about being a servant in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No. I liked it all - although I was awfully hard worked you know. Up early in the morning and - and - sort of on your feet all the time, but then of course I was young and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And all the different servants had their own jobs to do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, they'd their own jobs to do, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The cook just cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The cook just cooked, and when she - and her dy out - I had to put up the dinner, but it was pretty well ready for me you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about when the other people were off, who would do their jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, the table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15673613\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 maid would do the housemaid's job and - but the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Who would wait on table if she was off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The housemaid. Housemaid, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was the washing sent out or done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 All sent out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Who made or mended the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, they would mend their own if they - we had nothing to do with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And would they be made by a tailoress or would they buy them from a shop, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well I know their hats were - I mind because I minded them - showing me hats that they'd got from George Street, the four of them. The younger ones, hats the same in George Street, but their clothes, I don't know actually who made their clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about repairs in the house, who would see to the repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh had the - they - they never sewed, anyway I never saw any of them sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But actual repairs to the house, suppose a window got broken?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, I never - they were - didn't happen to be anything like that that time I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They don't if they got a joiner in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh they would if - if it was they had to get a joiner in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They wouldn't expect one of the servants to do it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, you see they were all girls, there were no men - servants at all. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The girls were all grown up by the time you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The youngest, Miss Littlejohn was twenty-six year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 So they didn't have a nanny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Where about did they eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well they ate in the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What kind of cooking equipment was in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh a big range. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it a coal fired one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A coal fired, a - oh a huge range, and a - a gas cooker
, which - they didna like using if possible, because the smell seemed to go up - the house, mm hm. If you were roasting meat in it - you could smell it all over the house, whereas in the in the range you didnae. Aye, I don't think it'd be very modern you 
know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
The breakfast was at eight o'clock in the morning. And - lunch - was a three course lunch, this is the Littlejohn's I'm talking about - the lunch was a three course lunch, at - half past twelve or so. And then the 
young - ladies had tea in the afternoon, we had nothing - I had nothing to do with that. We had our tea in the afternoon. And then a supper, and always plenty to eat. But the - at the Littlejohn's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you get the same as they got or different food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well - the - the - not - you'd - at the - every weekend - and the one week - end they had a - a sort round. Well it was the good - silverside and we had the salt round of brisket which was very good. And the - the next weekend it was roast mutton, and
 next weekend it was roast beef. And we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And would you get a bit of the mutton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Yes, we'd the beef and the mutton. The only difference was when we had the - the sirloin - they had and we had the sil - they had the silverside, and we had the bri
sket you know. Mm. But it was always very nice, you know. Of course - I enjoyed it then, I maybe wouldna enjoy it so well now you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did all the family eat together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 All the family ate together. And all the servants ate together in the servants ha.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What would they have for their breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well, they'd always a choice, there were a - a - hotplate on the sideboard, and there were always scrambled egg, bacon and egg or poached egg, different things, and the young ladies as they come 
down - went and helped themselves. To what they fancied. Sometimes kippers you know, they were fond of kippers and that, and - a lot of them didna take anything except coffee in the morning, coffee and toast, yes. But - uh huh, they'd the percolat}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15673613\charrsid9520696 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 r, it was - Miss Littlejohn made it herself at the table -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15673613\charrsid9520696 
 in the morning in the percolato}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 r.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 On a Sunday, they had a big meal at lunch time on a Sunday did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They had - you know, they had - they had the same - they had the cold meat on the Sunday fo
r lunch, and curds and cream and fruit, the snow lying on the ground and the - and the curds on a Sunday, and - the cream I suppose when they were young - they had fought about the cream, you get more than me, before you come to my turn it will be done, a
n
d the cream came in wee cans like that, and at each - plate - at each - place on the table there were this wee can of cream for each of them and they'd their own - and that was right on when I was there. They never stopped it. Because they'd quarrelled ab
out who was getting the most cream. By the time it come to the last one there'd likely be none left in the jug. So they were sure they would all have their own.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were any of the following made in the house, bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No bread, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Jam,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Jam, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Bottle fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Who would make all these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh the cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they grow fruit and vegetables in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
There were no garden. No garden. Oh well there were ever so big - drying place but no garden. Oh no, no garden, no. No at Royal Circus, no. Not - not - no. The - the back door you went up a few steps to a sot of drying green.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Who looked after the drying green then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I never saw anybody look after it. And there were a wash house, outside, at the green.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Fruit and vegetables would be bought for the household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, Miss Littlejohn did shopping every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She did the shopping herself did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh she went - ordered it, yes, and of course it was sent. Went and saw what was coming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it always fresh fruit and vegetables or did she ever buy tins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, never saw a tin - I never - werena tins in these days very much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have meat every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Always fresh meat was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Fresh meat every day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And the servants ate in the servants hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember Christmas Day, did the family do anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well, we got - got - I got presents from all the - young ladies on Christmas Day, gloves and scent - bottles and - and - wee photo frames and different things from them all. And of course we'd a Christmas dinner you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And the family would have a Christmas dinner as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they go to church in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They did - they - there were only one of them that ever went to the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they ever do anything special, did they have visitors in on Christmas Day or did they go out visiting or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, the - we didnna - no, we - we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The family itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, nothing special, no. No. There were one daughter - Miss Beatrice, and she was an almoner in a hospital, a
nd she would come in the morning and spend Christmas Day with them. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No - well they had the piano in the drawing room but I - they didnae - they wasnae musical.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They didn't have sing-songs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, nothing no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They had books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, they'd a library of course, a library in the house - one wall - oh just full of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And newspapers and magazines?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Never saw many magazines and - newspapers either - lying about, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you remember them reading out loud at all to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, of course you see I was downstairs and they were up in the - drawing room or the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, not - not - in - but just before I went one of the ladies died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But not after you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, just before I went she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever go out with Miss Littlejohn at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, not with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 There were never any outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not - not - not with they, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did Sir Henry Littlejohn or Miss Littlejohn think it was wrong to work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, a Sunday was kept sort of special like enough, you see, there were always so many out on a 
Sunday - just two in on a Sunday and three out, different Sundays.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And Sir Henry sometimes went to church did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Sir Henry - now he didnae go very much to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 One you said that went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. Miss - she married the - Minister there. Well I think the two - younger ones sometimes used to go to the - St Johns at the West End.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever go to the same church as they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, I went always to Lawrence Street church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about the other servants, did any of them ever go to the same church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. The - one of them went to the congregational out at - Gorgie way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But not the same church as the ladies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. I was the only one that went to that one and just because I had been in the habit of going. And I li
ked the - Mr Lawrence and I liked to go to hear him preaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they say grace at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I don't know, I was - no, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 In the servants hall did they ever say grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They had family prayers on a Sunday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Sunday - every - morning. Every morning. Every morning yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did the servants have to go to it as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, we'd to go in to prayers on a Sunday - every morning, a certain time. They sounded the gong, and we went up and p
rayers and had to - kneel down while he was saying the prayer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That was Sir Henry that took them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Sir Henry, yes. And he read the Bible and - said the prayer, and then - on a Sunday morning and a Sunday night too. Sunday - night was the only time - night was a Sunday. The other times we had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were Sir Henry or Miss Littlejohn interested in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, I never heard them anything about that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they take part in any kind of sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever see them playing cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Never saw them playing cards, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you know if he went to a club of any kind?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. He was a lecturer you see in the university when I was there and - his -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 So possibly it was the university club that he might have gone to for his meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He might - he'd be to - yes. I wouldna know where they were when they were out of course. Mm. hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Miss Littlejohn would be allowed to go out on her own if she wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh all the - all the ladies went out on their own if they wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they do any work for charity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, they were - they served in the soup kitchen, the two younger ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Whereabouts was that, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 About in - the Lawn Market there, down about that way, and
 then they went to some place - what was the post house, is now the Western General, and two of them went there - certain days in the week. And helped, they did something there, I don't know what they did, but they went - it was really the post house, at 
- when I was at Littlejohn's. But now it's the Western General hospital.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Sir Henry was a lecturer at the University?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, he lectured in the summer. And - we had to be up early - for he went early out - than - oh his - days that he was lecturing,
 and he always - end of the season, he gave the table maid a pound - for having to get up early. And when we were in Arlecha - I was coming in at the gate - I'd love to see A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15673613\charrsid9520696 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 lecha again, I'd love - to see that house again, and coming in at the gate I met 
sir Henry and his two sisters, and he said, oh he says, I always went with you, and he gave me a ten shilling - piece, he says, that's for getting up early, but it's without the knowledge of my daughters mind this is. And I had the ten shillings for getti
ng up early when he was lecturing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You said he was the first Medical Officer of Health for Edinburgh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Yes, the first Medical Officer of Health Edinburgh ever had. He introduced an awful lot of things - that are quite common now you know, disinfectant and - and injections and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was he ever away from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He never was away from home the time I was there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have friends who called to visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, the young ladies had friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have people to stay with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, occasionally, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they ever have a dance or a ball in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not in the house, no. But the young ladies went to dances. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And they would all get dressed up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 All get dressed up in their evening dress, yes, mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What kind of people called on them, what kind of people were their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, for one - were - the Curry's that had the - shipping - yes, and they stayed down at the foot end of Leith Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They've just sold that place now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Did they? Aye well, they were quite - regular visitors, yes, and other ones but I don't know - came out, but I knew the Curry's because we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You'd say they were the same sot of class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, all the same sort. I expect they were anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What class would you call that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, the better class definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Because of the jobs they had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, mm hm. You see, none of the Littlejohn's except Miss Beatrice - did any job at all outside, except 
the other ones doing charity jobs. They didn't do any thing for money or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they treat any of their friends differently from any others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well you see I wasna there when they had their friends, I was down - down below you know, I didnae -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about the guests, how did they treat you? Were they any different from Sir Henry and Miss Littlejohn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, you see I would only - see the guests when - maybe I'm helping in the forenoon. Then I wouldnae see them again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Would they speak to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, good - morning, ask you how you were sometimes you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They were quite friendly towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They didn't treat you as just the servant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no, no, were - they just were nice with you you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You think Sir Henry was quite content with his station in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Because he had got on so well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He wouldn't necessarily have liked a higher position you don't think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well of course - he was an old man by the time I was with him you know. He was over seventy the time I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Had you ever known anybody like him before you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, I hadna met anybody to know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did you think about them and their way of life, being so different from your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well of course it was - very strange to be - to begin with and - and I was quite charmed with the different food and the - girls all being so nice to me and the young ladies being so nice to me, I thought I would be sort
 of like what you read about in the slaves you know, and it was nothing like that at all. They were awful nice to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did their general behaviour seem totally different from what you were accustomed to
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well I didn't have anything much to do wit
h them in that way, as I say I was up the stair in the forenoon, doing the rooms, and then I didna come in contact with them again - until the next forenoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was a much better life than you thought it was going to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. Oh yes, I liked it very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you first get your job at Royal Circus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was advertised for a girl, and - I went and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 In a paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was advertised in the Evening News, and I went - after it, and - it was Miss Littlejohn that interviewed me, mi
nd she asked me all the questions if ever I had toothache and - yes, aye, she didna want to be bothered paying anybody that was ill often. So - she practically engaged me on the spot you know. If I was good at cleaning brasses and - asked me a lot of ques
t
ions you know and of course I had been used to working a lot at home, and - it came quite natural to me. I didna take nearly so ill with it as anybody that had been brought up with a nice mother and - you know, better - looked after. We were looked after 
well enough as regards being kept clean and - and dressed and that, but we didna get any kindness you know, and we were made to work and - do things that other mothers wouldnae have maybe bothered us with - doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You were there for about two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
I was really when I think of it I was a bit more than two year, I went in the month of - November, I think it was Nov - or Novem - no, I went in the month of - January and I didna leave until November, I was two year and these months. Almost three year
s I was there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You said you stayed there longer than other people had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Yes, you know they only stayed two month, and that - the - their mothers wouldnae let them stay. Do you know this, that I was only fourteen and there were the cellars do
wn the stair, and they had what they called the nursery, was what they had used when they were all young, and it still went under the name of the nursery was a great big plain room - you know, and linoleum on the floor - floor and - and - rugs, and the yo
u
ng ladies used to sit there and - sew and read and - that through the day. But it always went under the name of the nursery. Well I had that room to do in the morning. And I had coal to carry from the bottom of the house up for the top flat where the nurs
ery was, and they had - there were no bathroom in the house, no no bathroom.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it your job to take the water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, you'd to carry the water but one thing - half way up there were a little toilet place and a - a sink and - and taps with the wat
er. You had just half a flat to carry the water, but you'd the bath to set down in the room, and they had their bath and there were a screen, there were two in a room, and there were a screen that they could put round the bath, and - then in the morning y
ou'd all this to empty, carry away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How often did they all have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
There were one had one every night you see. You would have it tonight and I would have it tomorrow night, the two that was in the room you see. Night about turn and - it was to set every night you know. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Why did you leave that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well - I was really just getting kind of the - I was getting - I could do - do with something better. You know, I was kind of growing up a wee bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you hear about your next job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well I went to the registry office in Chandwick Place, and - they gave me this address at Craiglockhart House and I went out right away, and I saw Sir Oliver and Lady Riddle, they take me into the library and interviewed me and the way t
hat - I really got the job, they were - awful anxious for somebody that could cook - that could send up the dinner on the cook's night out and on her Sunday off. Well I had been used to that, 'cos whenever - they asked me that and I said that I had - had 
t
hat to do, Lady Riddle said - oh - oh - dear, here's someone - could do the dinner and of course right away - they looked at my character and I was very nearly no getting a char - at least Miss Littlejohn said no. She'd a big - window, and inside this win
dow there were a - a c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15673613\charrsid9520696 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
nary, and it was built in, you know, a - a cage in it, a bird cage, and in the bottom she'd a tortoise. Well you wasn't supposed to go upstairs unless you were pressed, and it was kind of early, and I had ran up and I had a wee fringe
 and I had two curling pins in, and I ran up the stairs for to see if the fire was burning all right, and she - when I was down on my knees looking at the fire Miss Littlejohn came in her dressing gown to see the canary and the tortoise, and she was in go
o
d cut that morning because she says to me, have you ever seen my little tortoise Helen? Oh and fumbled before I turned round to try - and I couldna get them out in time and I'd to turn round with my curlers in, I never saw the tortoise yet. Oh she got on 
t
o me tooth and nail. When they've - she knew I was leaving at that time, when - anybody writes for your character I'll tell them you're disobedient. And of course I was - but she didna you know, she give me a splendid character, she just said that you kno
w at the spur of the moment. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 So you went to Sir Henry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Craiglockhard House. Slate - it's at Slateford. The one - lodge gate was in Slateford, and the other was just a wee bit from Craiglockhart church, down the hill. It's all bungalows - now
, well when I was there there were a coachman and three grooms, and a head gardener and five other gardeners, employed on the estate. Mm. Great big gardens they were. And he gave the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A big house as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye, the house was a - a good size too of course there were only the lady and gentleman, and a lot of the rooms were never used you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They had no family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No family, no. Lady Riddle went through several operations and eventually he just wouldn't have her go through any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you better paid at this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh yes, oh much better. Twenty pound in the year. Five pound - in the three month I had to start with. And then I got it up and I didna mind that. I think I had about twenty six pound in the year when I left, which was considered quite good then you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well of course - you only worked - you did your work - what you had to do, and I had the rooms that werena used all to keep, well Sundays they didna need hardly anyth
ing, just - the duster over them you know, and - I'd always the front door and the - the - a great square hall, and had a log fire, always logs they burned, well I had that to do and the front door, but that was always the first thing in t}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10103890\charrsid9520696 he morning. And I had the libr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
ary to do, and - then - come down here and I had the - the servants hall there too, I had the servants hall to do, and the rooms to keep that werena in use. The head housemaid kept the - the room, the one room of course there were this - the c
ouple - bedroom and dressing rooms, she kept that. But I had the stair, the - it was a carpeted stair of course, had that to sweep down and - the long - oh huge corridors, long corridors, to sweep and dust. But on the whole I had a very good time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And you got time off there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh you always - the same in - in the Littlejohn's you'd your time off too, every other Sunday and - and - one - night in the week, the same as - at Craiglockhart. It was a general rule that, one night in the week, and every other Sunday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have to be back by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well at Craiglockhart you were supposed to, but it more depended on the cook - who was the boss - than the lady of the house, she didna know when you came in, she never bothered. B
ut - the cook of course - and I was young and she thought I was sort of under her care. And I mind she was only forty-two, she said she had twice come of age, and I thought that was an old woman. And she was - and she used to wear a bonnet and - and - alw
ays a black costume when she went out, and white petticoat. Oh beautiful white underclothes and she used to - uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have any special uniform when you were in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well you'd always to have a - a print proper in the morning, and a black dress white apron and cap in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did the owners of the houses supply these for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, oh no, you bought them in yourself. Oh no, you bought all that yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And if you wasted it you had to replace it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh yes, but we never - they did you a long time. You know. Did you a long time. And - some of them - I used to eventually make my own wrappers with the help - of the girls beside me, and one of them had a sewing machine and - they were - were all very hel
pful to me, but I - I had - I had no - no money troubles as regards that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about the other servants at Craiglockhart, now how many were there altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh there were just the four of us, there were the cook, and the housemaid and the tablemaid and me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You each had your own set jobs to do did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 We each had our own set jobs to do, and - some called me the under}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10103890\charrsid9520696 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 housemaid, but Sir Oliver objected to anybody being called under and I was called the second housemaid. But I had to he
lp the cook like at - when she was - out I had to do the - the dinner, but it was practically - well prepared. They were both on a sort of diet and both - Sir Oliver was very bad with his stomach, and had rabbit cream. Of course, they had two shooting lod
g
es. They had Mielville Castle, and Bayville Castle at Balerno, the two shooting lodges, and of course that was always the cook's got tired of the game and the rabbits, oh, rabbits, we - nearly shouldn't have been in force in the morning we'd so many rabbi
ts. All our friend could get rabbit - when they came to visit us, there was - 'cos the breast of the rabbit - was only used for the rabbit cream. Put thr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10103890\charrsid9520696 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 ugh this - and the rest, you know, quite -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was minced up was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, put through a sieve
. Yes. Fine as fine could be. And mixed up and steamed. That - but that - fried sole, a full sole, fried sole and rabbit cream, and sometimes a jelly. And there were always a glass of sherry - in the jelly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Any jelly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. When the cook made it 
there were a glass of sherry in it. But they hadna the sher - they hadna the sher - jelly very often. They just had the two courses, they lived very plain. But he was a millionaire. Oh yes, practically a millionaire. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You had a servants hall, that would be where you would eat and where you would sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well, no we ate in the kitchen really. Yes, the servants hall was quite a bit from the kitchen to carry - on a - a Saturday afternoon we always had our tea in the servants hall maybe, but for u
sual - well, we - we near - we had our tea in the night in the servants hall maybe, but our breakfast and our dinner we had in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Where}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10103890\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
about did Sir Oliver and Lady Riddle eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They ate in the dining room, yes, mm. And then they sat in the library after that at night or the drawing room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The two of them always ate together did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, they're a very very loving couple. A very affectionate couple.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What would they have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He had always a boiled egg
 and he boiled it himself. A wee pan - that was sticking up in the wee sort of - thing - swivel thing in the fire, and wee pan of water was sticking up there, of course they'd their own hens, and their own milk, they'd a dairy and everything, the coachman
 - milked the cow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 At Craiglockhart itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
At Craiglockhart yes, they had the cow and they had their own hens were kept down at the stables from the - the coachman and them looked after them. But there were always the fresh eggs came up and he h
ad a boiled egg. Porridge, and the meal had to be steeped the night before, and the porridge made - Lady Riddle didn't have the porridge, and - a boiled egg. And - they - she just - just - she just had toast and marmalade I suppose. He would have the - th
e - porridge and the boiled egg. And always he was out then away to his business, and Lady Riddle always for her lunch, she'd bacon and egg. Aye, aye. Bacon and egg and tea, she liked that for her lunch, mm hm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have the same food as them or something different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well it was kind of different in a way because they were on a sort of diet. But we werena, no, no, we did -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You could eat what you wanted more or less could you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, well it - it was ordered you see, we would have ste
ak and mince - and rabbit, and - hare, jugged hare and - stuffed hare which I didna like you know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Who did the ordering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well the cook - the Lady came down to the kitchen every day - to order what was - the menu for the - the day like and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did she decide what your work was to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well it was all decided when I was there - before I went there you see, my - job the one before me you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did she supervise you at all to see that you'd done it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Lady Riddle never interfer
ed. No. But if you broke anything, if it was Sir Oliver you went to tell, and he was always so nice. Oh well, and - and so kind, oh well you know you couldn't help it. But you were quite right to come and tell me, he would say. He was awfully nice. She wa
s more - she never interfered was very very quiet, and - and would seem more a shy - person. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They were both very kind to all the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh very kind, yes, very kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you feel fairly at ease with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - not - couldna - I 
couldna talk freely to her at all. She never - you know, she was always the Lady. But Sir Oliver sort of came down to your level you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you call him Sir Oliver?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If you spoke - if you did - good morning Sir Oliver, good morning my - your Ladyship, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did they call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Just your first name, they called me Helen. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And the same with the other servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, they - they were their first - Katherine was the maid and - and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10103890\charrsid9520696 
Brown - they get - because - Isa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 bella was her name, that's how they called her Brown, and the Cook was always just Cook. Just Cook. Didnae get the name, just Cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You enjoyed that job did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, I liked - yes, with that, I took a bad leg when I was there, and I had to
 go into the infirmary and I was eight month off, and I left them because - I was getting kind of older for that job too you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How long had you been there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh about seven years anyway. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You were friendly with the other servants were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Mm? Oh yes, kept on a - one of them - very nearly died in my house - lately, the table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10103890\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 maid - stayed with me quite a lot, eventually - staying with me when she had to be taken to a nursing home. And she died there in the nursing home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What happened to your pay at that time, what did you do with the money that you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh you just kept it for dressing yourself or going out. Or I - sometimes I tried to save but I never could save very much somehow or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It wasn't all that much was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It wasnae really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 About the washing at Craiglockhart, was it sent out or was it done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They - we did our own washing at Craiglockhart, our own personal washing. But the other washing all went to the laundry. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you know where the family got their clothes from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, Lady Riddle got her clothes - from Darling in Princes Street, and I think it was - Roma}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10103890\charrsid9520696 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 nes and Patterson. And - I'll tell you a story about this, she was presented - at the court, and of c
ourse they'd any amount of money, and she got the rig out from - two different shops, and she would try them on and he would tell her which she looked nice in. He said, now Jeannie I think you should wear that one, or Jeannie - Jeannie was her name, and h
e
 was always so nice to her, decided what frock to wear, well evidently - your dresses are described in the papers. And - the shops sends in the description. And - Darling sent in Lady Riddle wore so and so, and this other shop had in Lady Riddle wore so a
nd so. And of course it was the two - rigouts that she was described in well - caused quite of a - bother at the time, they were quite - vexed about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If she was dressing up to go anywhere did she let you all come and see what she looked like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No. She didnae. She - she - no, she didna do that, no. She was - she was really - very much - but very quiet and very nice, I never ever - never ever - spoke a wrong word to me all the time I was there. Never quarrelled me for anything anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did they cook in the house, what did the cook have to cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh, a huge range, and no cooker. Just this range in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She didn't have a gas cooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No gas cooker. The cooker at the Little john's of course was just a relic, it had an awful 
smell. Mm. But - the - they werena - they had nothing at the - Craiglockhart, except for the - oh huge range, it was nearly tall - not quite but an awful long range, and - a wee gas bunsen that you could - boil a kettle on in a hurry. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did the cook make bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was all bought in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 All bought in, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She did the ordering for the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well I suppose it - it - the cook - we got the - our groceries from Gibson in Princess Street, and the cook wrote out a line
, what she needed you see. And the - the Ladyship would take in. She went into the town - in the carriage every day, for -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about people that came to the door selling things, were they allowed to buy things from the door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I don't think that
 - they - they always came to the back door you see, they didn't come to the front door. But there were never a message came to the door - or a telegram which they used to get sometimes, but there were three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10103890\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 penny piece - for the boy, that brought it up. U
h hm. Oh they were awfully generous like that. But anybody selling things it was the back door, well it was up to us if we wanted anything or no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If somebody brought fresh vegetables to the back door would the cook be allowed to buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh wel
l of course we - had all - our own gardeners you see, we never had anything like that, no. And then - it was quite an avenue up - from the gate up, that there werena many - sometimes beggars came because they knew they got something. And they - the cook w
ould give them a glass of milk, we'd plenty milk and plent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10103890\charrsid9520696 y cream. Always cream to your p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 orridge and to your pudding and that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Even for the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes. Oh the lady never interfered with the cook you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did the cook make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, yes. 'Cos their own fruit would come out the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Would she bottle the fruit and vegetables as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I never saw anything bottled, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did she make pickles at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no pickling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Or wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Or medicines?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They didn't have to buy any vegetables then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, they come up from the garden, every day the gardener came up - with the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh of course the fruit w
as in the garden too, they'd great - greenhouse and - grapes and - peaches and things like that, uh huh. They'd all come up from the garden. See there were - six - five gard - gardeners and a head gardener. Was six gardeners you know. And beautiful garden
 
- oh lovely roses and - flowers came up twice a week. The gardener brought them up and he did them, he put them in the vases, the vases were all taken along to the - tablemaid's pantry, and she did all the - flowers, and he always got a glass of whisky wh
en he was down. A glass of whisky always left for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They kept hens and they kept cows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 One cow, just one cow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have any pigs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Any what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no pigs, no. They'd a - there were a that - there were a 
pond - and there were ducks, and ducks in the pond but just ornamental you know. The ducks were all right, but - it's - they'd just the cow and the hens sort of. But oh they were very - particular, for instance one of Ushers died, and Harley the coachman 
c
ame up with the carriage as usual, had he had brown reins - on the horses, and Sir Oliver said sent them back to put black ones on. Mm hm. To put the black reins on. And - Harley was very reluctant to do it. Oh sir, Oliver - nobody'll ever notice. I want 
the black ones, he said, we're going along Princes Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was this actually a relation of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
He was the senior partner of Ushers and of course - they were all very very - friendly, they werena related. But - he was the senior - he was r
eally the head of Ushers. The distillers, not the brewers. Very annoyed if you thought he was in the brewery. Ah, but the - the - the distillery, oh no, you're corrected right away, if anybody thought he was in the brewery.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember if you did anything special on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well at Christmas Day, of course all the - the - people on the estate, they all got a roast of beef, and a plum - and - a - a - bottle of - port, and the Christmas Day of course we had a special dinner, and a bott
le of port for the servants. And they went to the church of course they went to the church regular, every Sunday and they wouldna take the coachman, a cab - came to take them to church on to Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was this to save them working in a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I suppose so, the church in Collington but anyway a cabman was working on a Sunday. Give the - give the coachman the day off you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember if there were any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh there were a grand piano. A grand piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did anybody play it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, Lady Riddle sometimes I heard her playing hymns on a Sunday night. But never - at any - through the week I never heard her at it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They had a library in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh a huge library.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They probably had newspapers and magazines as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh the newspaper come in of the night. And she always got these - big books, I don't think they're on the go - a few of them - and big - magazines she got. I mind the \{BLANK\} was one of the, all the - pictures all of fa
shion, she was very fond - very fond of dress, and always - books for the different fashions and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you remember a funeral in the family itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, not the time I was there. No. But - aye, b
ut they - then that wasna in the house you see, but after I went away of course Sir Oliver died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But that was after you left?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And La - Lady Riddle only lived ten month after him. She was ten years younger than him, but she only lived ten month after him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever go away with them on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh no. They went every year in the spring - they went to Bournemouth for six weeks, and the spring cleaning was done. The men came in and lifted the carpets and took down the pictures and all
 that. And then in the summer they went to Oban. And then in September they went to Fishers Hotel, Pitlocharie. Three different places they went regular each time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they take any of the servants with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. The time they were away, in the 
spring, we did the house - the cleaning. In the summer we too had holiday, and two was at home. And we sort of cleaned up a wee bit, and then in the - in the autumn, well, there were nothing then, they just - we just had the time to ourselves, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you had a holiday were you paid while you were off, you still got your pay did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes. And always a pound to spend on our holiday. Mm hm. Which was - seemed an awful lot in these days. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They went to church did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh they went to church every Sunday, yes. They went to the church in Collington, the English church. Yes, mmm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they ever take any of the servants with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 To the church? Oh no, we went to Craiglockhart church, the tablemaid and I was always ou
t together and we'd holidays together and everything. And we went to Craiglockhart church. And - and the other two went to the church in Slateford. It's - done away with now, the church in Slateford, St Widmill or something. Aye. Away, an old church then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well I never really saw them start their meal, I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they ever have family prayers like the Littlejohn's had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, not - no, not - not - that we know of you know. We werena called in, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were they interested at all in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Yes. He was a great - very keen - on polit - when there were an election on. The gardener and him used to go at it teeth and nail. Arguing about the different I mind Mr Frank Usher - was one that was trying,
 and I canna mind who the other one was. But - the coachman, of course he always went to the boss, whatever he was - with which one was, the same as master, well they didna what the master was he was the same as master, and he of course was a very - strai
g
htforward man, he kept to what he presented and - the - the vote in Collington and of course Harley, the coachman was up - had been driving somebody for his party, and Dewer, coming to the same place of course he was a driving, booing and booing at him, t
hinking he had seen - and he was only getting - brought back with the Harley with the rest of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was that Tory that Sir Oliver was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Tory, yes. Aye. So - I mind Frank - Mr Frank Usher - one of the Usher's, it was him that was standing to get in
, but I don't think he got in that time. I don't think it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did Sir Oliver take part in any kind of sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no. To tell the truth he was rather a delicate man. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He didn't ever go to races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, never anything like that, no
, he'd no - and of course we'd no wireless or television or anything like that at that time you know. No - no even any wireless.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did Lady Riddle go out on her own at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Never her - never on her own, she went every day - she - the carriage 
came up at three o'clock, and she went into the office - and collected him, at three o'clock, and the two of them, I think - maybe she went and got her hair done, I think something she did, I could see - that she'd her hair done, or they might have visite
d anybody, and came back, but they'd always afternoon tea when they come back, hot scones and - and - wee - they didna go in for any cakes, I mind they had the hot scones and the tea. Always the silver tray and the silver -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they take that in the dining room or did they have tat in the parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They had that in the - in the library. Aye, they just sat in the library and ate it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Then they had dinner at night did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Dinner in the dining room at night, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did she have any interests at all outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She had nae - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She wasn't interested in any of the charities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I don't think so, she - oh - very generous - they were in giving - to charity but didn't actually work in - help - help in - 
the working of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did the two of them go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well out to dinner together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 To visit friends mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye. Aye, mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He was a director?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He was the head - yes, he was the - the - head one in Usher. Yes. Mm. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he ever go away from home other than on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no. No. He was the senior partner in - in Ushers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have friends who called on them in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, they used to have ladies call in the afternoon sometimes.
 As a matter of fact Miss Littlejohn that I was with called one afternoon. Well I - I didn't - you see, I didn't open the door, the table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10103890\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 maid did that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they call for afternoon tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, if they - if they - were at - in - in the afternoon they got afternoon tea you see used to bring in to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have friends for dinner at night sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - if they'd parties but - always a big party, maybe twenty. And - the - a chief came in and cooked the dinner. And - the - extra t
able maids and that came in, waiters - came in to help and - had - had - somebody came to - from Princes Street to decorate the table with the flowers and that. And then there were the two tonight and tomorrow night you see, with the same decorations and 
that did, they would use the library for their breakfast - for that one day. Mm hm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they ever have people staying overnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh the - just relatives. Relatives in England came, stayed overnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The people that called on them, their friends, did they belong to the same sort of class as them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, oh yes, mm. They might not just have been - had so much money as them but - they were all ladies and - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did the guests treat you any differently from Sir Oliver and Lady Riddle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No, they - they - they always spoke nice to you and - asked how you were keeping and - and that you know. But there were always the same ones you see, they were always relatives - coming back, and the long time I was there you got - they got to 
know you and - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Would you say they were any different really from Sir Henry Littlejohn as people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well they were quite different people from the - the - the - the Littlejohn - daughters were all young and - well they werena so just the young, but they were full of life and that, and of course was a very quiet house at Criaglockhard, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Which one did you really like working for best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh Craiglockhart then. And I liked the Littlejohn's - as a - but then, I had so much easier a ti
me at Craiglockhart that I liked it. But as a family as I liked the Littlejohn's. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it seven or eight years you stayed there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye, it was that anyway. And then I took ill, had a bad leg, and I went into the infirmary. And then I was eight 
month off work, and I left then. And - I wen to Lochryn House at Craiglockhart Terrace. I wasna very long there, to a Mr and Mrs Stewart. And - I was there I think for about - two year or three year. And I got - I got married - from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was 1913 you were married was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 1913.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 So in 1911 you'd be in Lochryn House?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That was the year the census was taken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, I'd be in - yes, I remember that. I can mind - Mistress Stewart calling us into the - library there to ask 
my age and - all - where I was born - and - yes, I mind of that, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of house was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well, it was a new house built - just for them. But - a funny kind of house, the couple never - they were weeks and never spoke to one another a
t all. Never. He'd write a - if he was - he was - having a party he would write in a paper and put it up on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696  mantle
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
piece, so many gentlemen coming - to dinner a certain night. That was all. And there were two sons, an awful nice boy, Imrie, I was awf
ully fond of him, and Alexander who wasnae at home, he was at the - away at the school, and Imrie, and Imrie used to write to his mother when she was away. Sent his love and in which daddy joins, and I don't think - he showed me the letter he was writing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How old was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He - he'd be fifteen them. Mm. Fifteen then. He was killed in the - in the war, in an aeroplane, in the aerodrome, mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How many servants did they have in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Three. Cook and a housemaid and table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 maid. I was house - I was - on my own then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What was the name of the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Stuart. Stuart. Stuart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He - he was in the government, what was he - he was in the government something. He went round all the - places inspec
ting the food, and that. Uh huh. 'Cos I mind he took the notion - he had tasted peas broes in some of the places and he took the notion to that, 'cos I mind of them having that for a - but - oh they - oh she was a very nice - she was one of the Haigs of -
 but - Haig was her cousin, that - what was his name again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was your life much different at Lochryn House with the Stuarts than it had been?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well of course I had a lot more to do, but I liked it very much, you know, you're no - you were under no
body or anything, you were on your own then. That was the only - where I was really, before - I was sort of - the - the other housemaid, although, as I say, you werenae counted as under, a second to help but - at - Lochryn you had to do everything on your
 own, make your own decisions and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did Mrs Stuart supervise you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh not very much in as long as you did your work she didna bother you, no. She was really very - a - a - very very nice lady, she was a lady definitely. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did you get paid at that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh I think I would have nearer - twenty-eight pound I think, I knew I got a rise from Craiglockhart, I think I had twenty-eight pound then, yes - in the year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you get paid every month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Every month. Every month. Every month, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were there any ways that the job at Lochryn House was different, other than that you had your own job to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well of course they lived quite differently. The - the - they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They weren't so well off of course were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well they werena so well off for one thing, and another thing - they went in for much bigger meals, you know, at dinner they had all three or four course whereas at - at Craiglockhart they lived very very plain. Not - for the want of money, just b
ecause it suited them that way. But at Lochryn had - always a three - three or four course every night. And fruit and all the finger bowls on the table you know, and - lived very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about your food there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh very very good. Very good. Th
e cook always wondered if we were allowed meat at - to our supper at night, but - Mrs Stuart one day, there were a - a piece of - jig get, you know the different chops and she was courting them out to see if there were enough and she said, and three for y
ourselves for night. So she knew - then that it was quite all right us having a bit of meat at night to our supper too. Oh yes, we were treated very well at Lochryn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Even if they were not speaking did they eat together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh they would eat togethe
r, yes, but they weren't - would never - they would never - the boy would be at the table, he would make jokes and that, he was - nice, but - oh there were weeks they never spoke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have much freedom in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Far more freedom than any place. Far more freedom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You still had your day off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It's - your day off and your Sunday off and as long - if - the housemaid - the table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 maid, if - I wanted to go out she would make down the bed for me and that you know, and I would do her - 
but I couldna do the table, I did the table, but I couldna do the table without them knowing, but she could do - she could - put in the bottles in the bed and - with the - help each other out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you like being in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, I liked it. I quite enjoyed it the time I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about the washing there, was it done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No. Every - every - yes, no, everything was sent to the laundry, all - our clothes, servants clothes were sent to the laundry too. You were allowed so much in the week - laundry work you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 By the time you went there there wouldn't be a servant who would look after the boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, oh he - he was finishing the school, when I was there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They ate their meals in the dining room did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, in the night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did the cook use for cooking on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 A range - no - no buns}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 en nor no - nothing but the range this time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They had breakfast together did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye, they - they had - they - oh well, no, they - he alw
ays had it first, and the boys - Mrs Stuart was always late in coming down. Not until well after nine perhaps.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But she came down for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 She didn't have it in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, she hadne it brought up unless she wasna well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What would they have for their breakfast usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh bacon and egg, sausage and just the - a variety you know, but it - they'd no hotplate like what they had at the Littlejohn's you know. It was just kept - warm until she sent down for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about lunchtime, did he come home for his lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, very very rarely. But he always took something with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 
him. He was awful fond of cocoa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696  and he had - he took a thermos flask of cocoa with - along with him, and maybe sandwiches or - a scone or something like 
that. And he always of course was back for his dinner at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have a garden in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well no - no vegetable, just flowers. Mrs Stuart was awfully fond of flowers and gardening. She worked away in it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 So they'd have to buy all the vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 All the vegetables was brought, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Who did the ordering for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh Mrs Stuart herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it delivered to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Delivered to the house, yes. Mm. She came in every day to the kitche
n at a certain time to go over the larder with the cook, you know, to decide what was to before the dinner and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Christmas days and birthdays, did they do anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well on - on - Christmas Day, I didna mind much about Lochryn, wheth
er we'd anything special or no. We'd have a Christmas Dinner like - and we all got a present, and I remember getting a lovely locket one time, and handkerchie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 s another time, at the Christmas.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They had a librar
y too, but this - on a very small scale. Just a bookcase, they called the room the library, but there were a bookcase in the library but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you ever remember a funeral in that family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, there werenae a funeral in that family the time I was there, 'cos the boy was killed after I left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they go to church on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. Matter of fact they went to the same church as I went to, Craiglockhart church. The one - on the hill down from Craiglockhart. And -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have a special seat in the church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No, they hadnae special seat, they just went into any seat. We - and - she used to - didna like the window open and she used to shut the window if it was at the side of her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever sit beside them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they say grace at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Family prayers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No, nothing - I don't think so, they werena that type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about politics, were they interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not that I know of, no, I don't think so, there were nothing - special - turned up to be interested the time I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about sport or races?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, he was a great one for croquet. A great hockey 
player. Yes. But - I didn't know Mrs Stuart going in for anything. But he played hockey always, went in for competitions and that. Oh we knew right away whenever he opened the door to him if he'd lost or won. By his - he threw his things about you know if
 he had lost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did Mrs Stuart go out on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, quite often, yes, she went out quite a bit you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Where would she go, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh would be visiting friends. She'd a sister in the town too and she'd - quite a lot of friends, Mrs Stuart had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did she work for any charities that you know of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well - I don't know if she worked for any charity but one thing she did, we always saved our Christmas cards for her, and she cut out little - jokes of - saying or recipes out of 
books and pasted them onto the Christmas cards and they were sent to the hospital, and they made reading for those that werenae able to hold up a book. They'd all these jokes or - or anecdotes in them. I knew she did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Very very rarely. They didna go out together unless they were going to a dinner. Invited dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He worked for the Ministry of Food was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The Min - he's the min - the govern - the local government board or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he ever stay away from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well he sometimes went away from home fishing, but I don't - I don't know if he went at all - away on business at all. But he often went away for fishing holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If he was away on holiday did it make any difference to the way the house was run?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not the way the house was run, you just had less to do. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have friends who called on them sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, was - quite often that friends - and they'd quite often friends to dinner. Far far oftener than the Craiglockhart people had.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they go out to dinner as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, they went out to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have people staying with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, was quite often staying with them and - and - the boy had often a friend came to stay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The people that came to visit them, did they belong to the same class as themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Yes, and they came - to - generally when there were hockey - matches on, they - they'd always the house was full - of - friends for this hockey thing. They would be interested in it too you see, they would play too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of people would be their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well they came from England, I don't know what they did. But they were - really gentry, the same as what they were you know. Yes, mm hm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they treat all their visitors and friends the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh - well the same because they - the food was always so good, you know, and a - with - we'd a - a splendid cook of course, was - trained at Athel Crescent and that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did the guests treat you just the same as the Stuarts did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 The what, the guests? Oh - well they - they spoke to you but they didna - you know, you didna have any much conversation with them, no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You had to keep your place more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you think the Stuarts were content with their station in life, or do you think they would rather have been higher up the ladder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I - as things go they were quite high up you know. He was - of good family, Stuarts you know and - Mrs Stuart was one of the Haigs 
you know. She had been quite well brought up you know. And they got that house built for themselves. It's at the end of Craiglockhart Terrace. It is now a hotel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you get that job, was it another one that was advertised?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, of cour
se I was at home after having - my leg bad, and - I went I think to the register again when I was going to start again. And they gave me that address. But that was the only one I was at, the only address they gave me and I got there. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You were married in 1913?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Have you worked since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no, never worked since then. No, never worked since then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you enjoy being in service or would you rather have done something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well I never had any choice you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If you'd had your choice what would you have liked to have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
I don't know, I used to think it would be awfully nice to serve in a shop but - I - I think you learn more in - being a servant. You learn a lot of things you know from - the way that th
e - people better off than you, conduct themselves you know, and you - you can learn to talk to anybody better and that and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You never actually had any training for the job did you, just once you started you learned what to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Once I was started that was all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you first started with Sir Henry, who was it that showed you what to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh one of the other girls - tell me what to do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever belong to any trade union at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you think once you were in full time work, once you became a domestic servant, did it change your attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh no, of course - that time I met - met my - my husband that I - and eventually we got engaged, was two year engaged - before we were married and - 
of course and I was out of - we had different interests you know, we'd - go to theatre and - places together and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 After you left school you went into service so you didn't really live at home at all then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well, after I left school of course I was - in - nearly a year in the stationers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You stayed at home at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, I stayed at home. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did starting full time work change your relationship at all with your father and your stepmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - yes,
 yes, not so much with my father. My father never paid an awful lot of attention to us, and my stepmother was nicer to us. Only visiting once a week, than when we were staying in the house. I think to tell the truth she was glad to get rid - of us out the
 house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did it make any difference to your sisters when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh - oh - of course I - I loved my - young sisters, you know, just bairns coming into the house when you were a wee bit grown up. Aye. Oh I loved them. No, it didna make an
y - oh they used to look for - used to call me - my bonnie Nellie, my bonnie Nellie when I used to go in. They used to hold a great love for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you spend your Sunday any differently once you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - the - what - when I started 
work you see, the one Sunday you got off, and the next Sunday you were on all day. The cook got off. And I had to take the cook's place, to a certain extent of course - that sounds big but it wasnae really. Because everything had - there was soup to warm 
u
p and vegetables to cook. I'd always vegetable to cook, and the dinner, and the dinner at night and as I told you before, you're supposed to keep the - oven hot for the roast, it was always - a hot roast or a hot meat of some kind, and then I would have t
o
 - mind the cooker. I wouldna - could get the oven to go right and that, and of course the smell went up and Miss Littlejohn used to get awfully annoyed. Oh I used to get an awful telling, and I couldn't get that fire to go somehow or another. No like the
 way the cook managed it. Of course mind I was quite young too you know for to - tackle these sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you had your Sunday off what would you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well when I had my Sunday off - I always went to the church. And I went to Lawrence
 Street church, I walked all the way from Royal Circus - to Lawrence Street church. You didn't have the whole Sunday off. You had the one Sunday in the forenoon and the next Sunday in the afternoon. Well then I went back, in my forenoon, went back and was
 in all the afternoon that the cook - the next Sunday I just got out in the afternoon, I would just go home, and spend the afternoon at home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you interested at all in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, never - I never really - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you were younger 
at school you used to sometimes go for walks and you would play outside or you spoke about going to see these pictures. Once you were at work and you had any spare time off did you do anything differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, when I was working in spare - of course 
I had no money to spend really. See, my money - just went home. And what I got was handed into the house at home. But - when I - when I - was off I just was home and - back again at night, that was all my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You didn't go out to enjoy yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no. Un - unless when my older sister and I went to this - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 C}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
inematograph or something called it, in Queen Street it was. A hall in Queen Street. It was really before - pictures - came into vogue. I was in Craig - I was in Craiglockhart before - pic - the first picture house opened in Princes Street. The Palace.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you go to it once it opened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Well - the - the - it so happened - there were a lady staying - and a nurse and two children, and the nurse took me - to the pictures, along with the two children one day. Mm. That was my first experience of the picture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did you think about it, was it a moving picture at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was a move - oh yes, it was the ordinary pictures that they have now, and oh I was quite fascinated with it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they have somebody playing the piano at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. A - an organ sort of thing, either a piano, I didna mind but there were a - they played an instrument anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 After you left school did you make any new friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well the girls I was beside. And - sometimes their visit - visitors that they had, the girls had - friendly with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever take any of your friends home with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not - at first, I - I - by the time I was at Craiglockhart - the table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 maid and I used to go home, used to go home for our tea and - sometimes other - girls that I knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it all girls or did you ever take any boys home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, not - not - oh no, not at - I never had any boy home, until the boy I was getting married to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your parents want to meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh they didna mind, but I think you know my stepmother, she didnae }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 ncourage you to bring people home. She didn't. Not - you know - it's quite different from your own mother. They - they're different altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You were married in 1913?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I would be twenty-seven or twenty-eight nearly. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How long had you known your husband when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 About three years. About three years I knew him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you meet him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well it's very - there were an old gamekeeper at Craiglockhart and his wife - died, and - he had an awful nice son, and to tell the truth I was a bit in love with the son, and he used to pay me a bit of attention, and th
e son - was two year older than me, and this gamekeeper was three year older than my own father, and of course - after his wife died he used to pay an awful lot of attention to me. And I thought - he thinks to himself that I'll be getting married to the s
o
n and - and - keep house for him sort of style. And instead of that he was wanting me for himself. And he asked me to the theatre this night. And the play was the Lights of London. - Oh I was fair attracted you know. He clapped his hands at all the - joke
s and everything, and had us in a good seat and everything, but I wouldna go unless the table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
maid came. So the three of us went, and - going into the theatre there's two - I knew one of the - chaps was at the - at the station, and his pal was with him, and
 he introduced us and we sat together, and that was the start of it, he came to see me after that. Evidently he - he thought when he saw me that - he must have liked me you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He really come from Glasgow. He was worki
ng in Edinburgh. He - he was an electrician at that time, or learning, in the station, working in the - in - in the Calley Station. But then of course - he was there until he went in there war, the war was only the year after I was married you see. Mm hm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he actually live in Edinburgh at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 Yes, he was in digs. In Holms}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696  Street, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 His actual home, did he change his home at all in the time that you knew him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - he was like myself, he was born on a Sunday morning at eigh
t o'clock, and his mother died that night at eight o'clock, and he was brought up with his granny. His father - went back - to say with his mother and that was Joe's granny you see, so he was brought up there and all the aunties - and uncles and that in t
he house, and made a great fuss you know with the - young life. Well one of - they all - eventually got married, and the last one that was getting married took Joe. That was him - staying with his auntie after that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was that still in Glasgow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Still in Glasgow, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he go home much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, if - he went home quite often at the weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 If he was at home did he ever write to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh, he would - I'd be seeing him in between you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You just met him when you could in Edinburgh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Yes. But - he had the sort of arrangement - with his aunt, that he would give her so much, until her oldest girl was working. And that sort of kept us kind of - he always made a her a little allowance, for having brought him up you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever go to visit his home at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes. Oh quite regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember the first time you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, that was before I was married. Yes. My sister - thats in - that was in California, she was going to California
, and we - I was seeing her off, and - my and met - met me and took me to his - aunties - in Glasgow. That was the first time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What sort of home did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh just an ordinary working class home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Much the same as your own was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, much the same as my own and - in fact to tell the truth I wold say no just \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 good as my own. No. But they were very nice people, but I didna like his au}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
tie very much somehow or other. I didn't - couldna say that I ever got fond \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 her or anything. But the uncle, his uncle was a particular nice man. Very very religious. But very very nice. I liked him awfully much. Deaf, he got awful deaf, although he was young, he was still bad at hearing you know, we used to shout to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they know that you were the girl that he was going to marry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh that - I was taken there on that - that was the idea when I went you see, that I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did they ask you many questions about yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, they never bothered you know, th
ey didna ask you any quest - they just sort of knew that I was in service and - they just thought I was good enough like, they didna bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What was his uncle's job at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He was a dry salter. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That's not a word we use nowadays is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I don't think it's in vogue at all now, now. But at that time it was a trade you know a dry salter. It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I think they're called ironmongers now aren't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, it is a sort of ironmonger, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was your husband brought up to go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh yes. His aunt was very religious, both his aunt and uncle - very religious. It was more mission things that they went to you know. Sort of mission halls they belonged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It wasn't the Church of Scotland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 They would re
ally be - Church of - they werenae Irish or anything like that, although his folk had - my - husband's folk originally came from Ireland. His granny came over from Ireland. The priest used to come and visit her although she was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you know what kind of mission it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, just one of these mission halls you know, they're all over. They probably were where I was too and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you went to visit his auntie did she let you have time alone with your husband to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no. Oh no. Yo
u see I had been seeing - then when I went to visit there the first time I had been seeing my sister away and I was - I wasnae very happy about it. And - we just were all sitting talking - I hadnae an awful long time there. And then after we went we just 
- we were just all sitting talking. Just be an afternoon - after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you treated as a guest or as one of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh as a guest I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did that change at all as time went on, after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, after I was m
arried I didn't see so very much of them really. You see, I - the war came on and - and - things was different somewhere or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did you actually call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - I - just auntie and uncle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It wasn't Mr and Mrs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, it was just the same as my husband called them auntie and uncle. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember the first time that your husband to be met your father and stepmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. He came - I - I was on holiday - staying at home, we were in Wheatfield Road of course, and
 he was going to take me a - an outing for the day, and he called for me to the house, and met them there, I mind he took me to Rosslyn - for the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Can you remember what happened when he met them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well - they just - no, there were nothing 
special, he was just treated like any visitor coming in. Wasnae long in of course, I was practically read to go. When he came, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he visit your parents much after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Not unless invited on a Sunday. Sometimes I had - I took him for tea on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He was the first boy that you'd ever taken home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 First boy I'd ever taken home, yes, uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your parents ever meet his aunt and uncle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. Not the uncle. The aunt when she came to stay with me for a wee while, I took her along to Wheatfield Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That was after you were married was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, after I married, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you first started courting, how often did you manage to see each together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well you see, my - night out was only once a week
, and every other Sunday. But then he usually used to come and see me - in between that. Au}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 e often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was he allowed into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, oh yes, the - the lady and - and - and the - in Lochryn House, and the boy were - used to call him the 
Bobby, I don't know why, but they - he was fifteen year old, and the - the gentleman's - cigars - were kept in a sideboard, in the kitchen, and he used to come for his father's cigar, and sometimes he handed Joe a cigar too. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you went out where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well often we went to the theatre, and we used - we never went dancing, he wasnae a dancer. But we went down to the Marine Gardens and watched them. And maybe had a cup of tea or a cup of coffee, and back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 As time went on did you do different sort of things or did you always do just much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well, we always did much the same, just always went out, mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did the table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 maid friend ever go with you or was it just the two of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh the table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 maid and I - that was - the - and - only one was out at a time at Lochryn, but at Craiglockhard, the table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 maid there and I was always out together, and we always went places together. And if by any chance we separated, we always met - at nine o'clock at the West 
End and went home together. Mind there were a long avenue, it was dark. It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever go on holiday while you were courting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - the table}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 maid and I always went on holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You didn't go with your future husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Never went - no. That wasnae really done then same as it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Do you remember any moment when you actually decided you were going to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - I think I do - remember you know just - thinking that - he was specially nice you know. And - and
 then of course when he asked me - marry me, he told me about his mother dying and being brought up with the auntie and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he actually say, will you marry me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He - he - it - it - he told me about his father, you know, and - his father mar
rying again and that and - he just thought - that he - he - he would like to marry me like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you surprised or were you expecting it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, I was kind of expect - I knew it was leading up to that. Yes, I knew it was leading up to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did he have to ask your father's permission?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. Oh yes, he went on the Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I - my stepmother and I went into the parlour, the time he was talking in the kitchen to my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Had you told your parents before hand that he'd be coming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Were you engaged then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Yes, I had a - beautiful engagement ring, I gave it to my granddaughter - when I came in here, because he got it made special, my birthday was in February, and he got the stones - you know, the round - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 amethysts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
 and the pearl - diamond in the middle, and a lovely - ring. And I thought it was a pity in here, to - you know, I might lose it. Or anything, so I gave it to my granddaughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you choose the ring or did he choose it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 He choose it. I didnae see it until he gave it to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did he know the size to get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well, we went back after - after I got it - we went back to the shop to get the - engraving inside, the date and - and our names inside. And so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 At that time could you be engaged without a ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well people would have an understanding with one another. If they hadnae a ring. Mm hm. Just the same - as - we - I was wee while before I knew - that I was marrying him before I actually got the ring. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever exchange any other kind of rings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No rings, no. They werenae so - that wasnae - popular the - then, as now exchanging rings, but we didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your husband didn't have a ring at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, no. Oh I don't think he would ever have worn a ring. He wasn't the type to go about with a ring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 When you became engaged did you have an announcement in the paper or a party?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No. No, no party, nothing, no, nothing, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did anyone give you presents at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Just the girls in the house where I was - gave me presents. Funny presents, one of them was a - a beautiful pair of scissors and in a case, and - a - a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have to give her a penny for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Aye, gave her - a - a coin, uh huh, and - the other give me a little black cat ornament you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did anyone give your husband presents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh not that I know of, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Once you were engaged did your parents treat you any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, no, of cours
e - no, they were just the same. You see, I was only home - on a Sun - and - and then - the tablemaid and I - had lots of other friends that we visited, and we visited together, and entertained them in the house together, at - at Craiglockhart, but at Loc
hryn - of course - well - were - every other Sunday was out at Lochryn too. I was just home and - meet - meeting Joe perhaps going a walk at night and back you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you choose your wedding ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - we went into a shop and - I choose - choose my wedding ring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 You both went together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, I try it on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 After you were married did you ever get an eternity ring or any other kind of ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Never had any other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever exchange tokens like Valentines or love spoons or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Not like that, but I would get a valentine, St Valentine's Day, yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you save up before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh I tried to save up, yes, I had to save up to - get -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Dud you find a house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh you got a house - very very easy at that - oh the - landlord would have taken you in a cab to go and visit one of his houses to get them - oh there were boards out at every - stair in the town nearly. At that - that - before the war you see. It was a
fter the war that the scarcity of houses came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you buy any household equipment before you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - yes, well - we both - went and saw the - sitting room suite and - dressers and things like that that we wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What about the smaller things, did you ever have a bottom drawer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, I got - ready and then - one of the girls at Craiglockhart, the housemaid that I was under, she ma}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 de nightdresses, a beautiful se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 wer and she made three - nightdresses all tucked you know an
d that, and - there was some - having the sewing thing in the church and they were making things and selling them, and I gave an order to the Minister's wife for three - sort of better ones, nightdresses and I had the half dozen nightdresses. And then oth
er things I just bought - bought special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 What did you actually keep your bottom drawer in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh just a nice - large pasteboard box. I had a trunk you see, for my own other things. And I would have so much in that and - and - you see, I didnae have a bottom drawer until I knew I was getting married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you ever collect china or cutlery or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No, I hadnae the chance to collect that. I hadn't any place - to put things. But I got china for - the - the - cook beside me, her sister - was the head one is Donald}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10497772\charrsid9520696 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
s at the - china place, there were a place about - near the infirmary, a big place. She was the head one there, and there were often broken sets that - like I mean, eleven - saucers or eleven cups and - and one - saucer missing or
 - or five cups and one saucer, and I got the chance of things like that from her often. Beautiful - some beautiful china I had, just not a full set. But they they couldna sell it - broken set, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did your parents help you at all in setting up your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Nothing at all, no. Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Who did you first see to arrange about your wedding?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh, well I think I - I went to different places to - see about it. We were married in Wheatfield Hall, and the Minister of Craiglockhart church 
married us, and went to different places, and then we'd a - we - decided to get the store to do the catering for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you arrange all the catering first or did you go and see the Minister first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh we'd see the Minister first to see - what - what suited him you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How long before the wedding did you actually go to see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh well - when I - ordered these nightdresses - the Minister's wife, she said - I told her - that I was getting married. Oh she said, that's nice, that'll be part of your trousseau we're making. And I said yes. So they knew you see that I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was that a good bit before your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh - not - not a lot of time. Six months maybe. Maybe - maybe four months. No quite six months I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was there any particular reason for the date that you chose for your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
No. The - you see, we - my time was up on the twenty-eight of May, you know, that was your term time, your pay time and that, and - it was to be - in a fortnight but I disc
overed it was the thirteenth of June, and I'm awfully superstitious and I had it the sixth of June. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 It was the hall of the church that you were married in was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. No. A - a hall, I think it's used for Salvation Army hall now. It's no really -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 But it was the Minister that married you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, the Minister of Craiglockhart church, that's the church I belonged to. I went to that church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 And you wanted a minister to marry you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh yes, I never thought of getting married any other way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have any difficulty in getting your parents to agree to you getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh no, they didna bother. They didna really bother. And then you see I wasnae. So young by that time, you know, I was - getting on.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Had you wanted a large or a small wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Oh well I wanted to have a wedding - a white wedding, I was sort of keen on that. I had a white - frock and a veil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How many people did you have at your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Fifty odd, fifty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you decide who was going to be invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well that was quite a problem. Because we couldna really invite the whole family. We'd to invite so many - the parents and - and that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you miss out children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No, we didn't - there were two children there, but on the whole it was all grown ups, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you decide how to split a family, was it the ones nearest in age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - well no, well we'd take the - the - parents, older - older members of the family, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Was it mostly relations that came to your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Quite a lot of relations, and quite a few came from Glasgow to the wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That was your husband's relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes, and - my cousin came from - not my cousin, a cousin of yours came Wishaw and and - then other c
ousins from Corstorphine here and - he had quite a few friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you decide that you were going to have half of his family and half of yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Left to me to make out invitations, but he told me who he would like invited. Then after that it was up to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How did you invite people at that time, did you send them a card?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 
Oh yes, you'd card - plenty of cards, the same as they have now. But maybe plainer, more likely, uh huh. There's - they'd no pin up you know, just a plain card.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Did you have anybody who stayed overnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 No. Oh yes, some of Joe's friends stayed overnight. The l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid73745\charrsid9520696 
andlady that he had had in Holms}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696  Street - put them up for a - for a night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 How were the costs of the wedding met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Well - I know - that - the - I - the - the cake - it was a three tiered cake, was nearly seven pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 That was expensive then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Yes. It was awfully expensive the cake, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Who paid for that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11013156 HH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 I did. Mm, I paid - I paid for everything myself for the wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14957223 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14813229\charrsid9520696 Your husband didn't contribute anything?
